This is the most complete FreQuency soundtrack I've found.

It has the main game tracks, the different menu tracks, and the developer-made remixes that were included with the game disc as possible starting points for making your own in the game.

(No, I don't know where Track #1 is, nor what it is, unless it's the European FreQuency exclusive track, "Why" by the group "Reeload". 
I would include that if I could, but I don't want to drop a YouTube recording in the middle of these 224-320kbps tracks.)

Anyone who downloads this, PLEASE seed past when you get ALL the files, but I will seed for quite a while, hopefully.

If you like the game as much as I do, you may like to have the songs that are in it, and if you haven't even heard of the game, I'd suggest you try it. 
Listening to these songs may help you decide whether you want to track down a copy of the game.

Related game info: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frequency_(video_game)
Source of files: Galbadia Hotel (http://gh.ffshrine.org/)
